<p><strong>Crucible Hornshield</strong>&nbsp;is a <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Greatshields" href="/Greatshields">Greatshield</a> in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wiki" href="/Elden+Ring+Wiki">Elden Ring</a>. The Crucible Hornshield&nbsp;is a <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Shields" href="/Shields">Shield</a> that scales primarily with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Strength" href="/Strength">Strength</a>. <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Greatshields" href="/Greatshields" target="">Greatshields</a> weigh a decent amount and provide the best protection in the game. <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Greatshields" href="/Greatshields" target="">Greatshields</a>&nbsp;provide a greater value of blocking and protecting one's self from enemy and boss attacks, but greatly increases the weight and reduces the player's mobility. This type of shield works best at reducing damage or guarding instead of parrying.</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <p><em>Greatshield of red-tinged gold carried by Crucible Knights.</em><br><em>Features a great horn.</em></p> 
 <p><em>An ancient holiness dwells within. The crucible horn skewers foes when performing shield bashes.</em></p> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Where to Find Elden Ring Crucible Hornshield</h3> 
<p>The <strong>Crucible Hornshield</strong>&nbsp;Shield can be found at the following location:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>Dropped by the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Lesser Crucible Knight" href="/Lesser+Crucible+Knight">Lesser Crucible Knight</a> patrolling the bridges of the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Siofra Aqueduct" href="/Siofra+Aqueduct">Siofra Aqueduct</a>. <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Interactive Map?id=1597&amp;lat=-172.296875&amp;lng=133.539646&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapB" href="/Interactive+Map?id=1597&amp;lat=-172.296875&amp;lng=133.539646&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapB">Elden Ring Interactive Map Link</a></li> 
 <li>Potential drop from the Lesser Crucible Knight found after the Rampart Tower bonfire. Travel towards the birds, and jump off the pillar towards some rocks. The Knight will be at the bottom of the cliffs.</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Elden Ring Crucible Hornshield Notes &amp; Tips</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Shield&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Skills" href="/Skills" target="">Skill</a>: <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Shield Bash" href="/Shield+Bash">Shield Bash</a></li> 
 <li>This&nbsp;shield cannot be infused with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ashes of War" href="/Ashes+of+War" target="">Ashes of War</a>.</li> 
 <li>Sell Value: <img style="width: 18px; height: 18px;" title="item_value_icon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_18px" src="/file/Elden-Ring/item_value_icon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_18px.png" alt="item value icon elden ring wiki guide 18px" width="18" height="18">&nbsp;500</li> 
 <li>Other notes and player tips go here</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Crucible Hornshield Upgrades in Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>Please see the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Upgrades" href="/Upgrades" target="">Upgrades</a> page to understand the weapon bolstering process.</p> 
<p>Requires regular reinforcement with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Somber Smithing Stones" href="/Somber+Smithing+Stones" target="">Somber Smithing Stones</a></p> 
<p>This upgrade can be enchanted with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Magic Spells" href="/Magic+Spells" target="">Magic</a> or boosted with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Consumables" href="/Consumables" target="">Consumables</a>.</p> 
